
[1]idolatrous

   IDOL'ATROUS, a. Pertaining to idolatry; partaking of the nature of
   idolatry, or of the worship of false gods; consisting in the worship of
   idols; as idolatrous worship.

   1. Consisting in or partaking of an excessive attachment or reverence;
   as an idolatrous veneration for antiquity.
